reviews.review: Not very original story but much better that The Last Jedi.  Glad they got rid of "Director" Rain Johnson (The Last Jedi) but JJ Abrams seems to screw everything up (Star Trek).  Please Disney, rethink who you have at the helm on these movies.

Plot 1/10 acting 2/10 graphics 9/10. 

Overall the final nail in the coffin for Disney's Star Wars.
Loved it. Such a touching end to a nearly 44 year saga.
Good conclusion to the sequel trilogy.  Poor pacing but still a good time at the movies.

You brought back The Emperor for this? Rey was the chosen one the whole time, not Anakin? Force ghosts can now interact with physical objects? Why not just rally the force ghosts to fight Palpatine then?

What do *you* think should happen in Episode 9? Whatever you just thought, that probably happens! And the opposite of it! And every other fan theory you've read is in there too! Everything that any person could possibly want is in this movie, not so everyone wins, but so no one does. It's not a bad time, but it's...a lot. It's confusing and frustrating and kinda nice pretty often, but ultimately...unsatisfying.

Star Wars: Rise of Skywalker has rendered the entirety of episodes 1-6 pointless... the amount of contrived garbage in the plot was unbearable, even as a fun action film it fails with underwhelming action sequences and a lack of lightsaber duels.
An overall disappointing end to a trilogy, and an insult to one of the greatest series of film ever made.

Unimaginative mess with too much exposition and forced character development. Palpatine seems to only be there because Disney wanted him to, not because it made sense or was necessary.
Worst film of the sequel trilogy and a disappointing end to the Skywalker saga.
it was kind of choppy and uneven, it also seemed to not have enough time for things while wasting time on less important stuff

I thought it was great. Sure, there were some plot holes, and a few things that I was confused about. BUT it very much felt like a Star Wars movie made for the fans. Countless nods to the old movies, and overall a great end to the series, all while cleaning up the mess of episode 8. Very happy with it.
